1
00:00:14,039 --> 00:00:15,400
Facing backwards is even more unlikely.

2
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:16,199
It's terrifying.

3
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:18,079
No normal person would ever do that.

4
00:00:18,199 --> 00:00:20,960
So when a person stands backwards up high,

5
00:00:21,399 --> 00:00:22,679
a woman's subconscious reaction

6
00:00:22,839 --> 00:00:24,519
is that her arms will involuntarily

7
00:00:24,519 --> 00:00:25,679
wrap tightly around her body.

8
00:00:27,199 --> 00:00:29,320
It's the brain's self-protection mechanism kicking in.

9
00:00:29,839 --> 00:00:31,039
I think men would do the same.

10
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:15,640
Officers,

11
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,680
please, have some tea.

12
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:19,040
Thank you.

13
00:01:22,959 --> 00:01:25,280
When I heard about Director Shen's suicide,

14
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:27,079
I was absolutely stunned.

15
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,879
No matter how big the trouble,

16
00:01:30,319 --> 00:01:31,879
she shouldn't have taken that path.

17
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:36,599
By the sound of it,

18
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,760
you believe Shen Qing committed suicide?

19
00:01:40,599 --> 00:01:41,560
It wasn't suicide?

20
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,560
Then could it be...

21
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:46,519
We're still investigating.

22
00:01:47,079 --> 00:01:48,519
We aren't ruling out any possibilities.

23
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:52,879
Did Director Shen exhibit any unusual behavior recently?

24
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,879
Unusual behavior?

25
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,560
Nothing really out of the ordinary.

26
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:03,319
President Su,

27
00:02:03,959 --> 00:02:05,200
the information you have

28
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,120
is crucial to solving this case.

29
00:02:07,799 --> 00:02:09,240
We need you to answer truthfully.

30
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,280
The thing is, some matters

31
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:16,120
involve the bank's

32
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,319
public image.

33
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,879
Which matters more, image or a life?

34
00:02:27,719 --> 00:02:29,680
A life, of course.

35
00:02:29,919 --> 00:02:30,680
So you see,

36
00:02:31,599 --> 00:02:33,319
withholding crucial leads

37
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:36,080
isn't as simple as avoiding trouble.

38
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,080
Officer, what you just said

39
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,960
really gives me a fright.

40
00:02:42,719 --> 00:02:43,520
The thing is,

41
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:46,120
this may not be tied to Shen Qing's death.

42
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,400
Director Shen, where are you?

43
00:02:48,759 --> 00:02:50,080
Oh, I stepped out to handle something.

44
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,319
I'm in a cab right now.

45
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,000
I'll be at the bank soon.

46
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:56,360
Come straight to my office when you arrive.

47
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,759
The Economic Crimes Unit is here.

48
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:00,240
They came to ask some questions.

49
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:21,840
Officers,

50
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:23,599
please have a seat.

51
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,039
Director Shen will be here shortly.

52
00:03:26,319 --> 00:03:27,280
Okay, thank you.

53
00:03:31,599 --> 00:03:32,240
Come in.

54
00:03:34,479 --> 00:03:36,560
Director Shen, come take a seat.

55
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,199
Let me introduce you.

56
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:41,360
These two

57
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,680
are from the Economic Crimes Unit.

58
00:03:44,199 --> 00:03:47,120
They're here about the Chengming Machinery loan.

59
00:03:48,759 --> 00:03:50,280
Li Ai, Economic Crimes Unit.

60
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,520
Director Shen, how much did Chengming Machinery borrow?

61
00:03:56,919 --> 00:03:57,919
Fifty-five million.

62
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,479
For such a large loan,

63
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:02,280
your bank's review of Chengming Machinery

64
00:04:02,599 --> 00:04:03,759
must have been very strict, right?

65
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:05,840
Oh, it was.

66
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,240
Extremely strict.

67
00:04:07,759 --> 00:04:09,080
Because the amount was so large,

68
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,800
from the moment I signed off,

69
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,639
I've been anxious ever since.

70
00:04:14,479 --> 00:04:16,279
The Chengming Machinery loan procedures,

71
00:04:16,279 --> 00:04:17,839
were they all handled by Director Shen personally?

72
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:19,759
The procedures were absolutely lawful and compliant.

73
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,560
I reviewed them carefully many times.

74
00:04:21,639 --> 00:04:22,560
There were no issues at all.

75
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,920
Then why didn't Chengming Machinery repay on time?

76
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,839
Well...

77
00:04:28,839 --> 00:04:30,199
They said the company ran out of money.

78
00:04:30,399 --> 00:04:32,439
Since Chengming Machinery's paperwork was fine,

79
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:35,160
that means their business was doing very well.

80
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,759
Otherwise, your bank

81
00:04:36,759 --> 00:04:38,959
wouldn't have lent them such a large sum.

82
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:39,680
Right?

83
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,040
According to our investigation,

84
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:44,560
the loan Chengming Machinery took from your bank

85
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,319
was not used for company operations,

86
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,759
and the company has long been operating in the red.

87
00:04:49,879 --> 00:04:53,199
Did your bank really know nothing about this?

88
00:04:56,399 --> 00:04:57,120
Director Shen,

89
00:04:57,759 --> 00:05:00,879
didn't you say Chengming Machinery's finances

90
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:03,439
were healthy and their operations had no issues?

91
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:08,560
The financial statements they submitted were detailed and credible.

92
00:05:09,439 --> 00:05:11,199
I also visited the company in person.

93
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,360
I didn't find any obvious problems.

94
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:17,120
Is it possible the financial statements were forged?

95
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:28,959
After the Economic Crimes officers left,

96
00:05:29,639 --> 00:05:31,759
I spoke with Director Shen alone.

97
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,120
She seemed a bit distracted,

98
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:37,920
and looked rather tense.

99
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,759
Now that I think about it,

100
00:05:39,759 --> 00:05:40,879
it does seem

101
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,920
like something was really wrong.

102
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,639
On this matter,

103
00:05:45,839 --> 00:05:47,360
you put a lot of pressure on Director Shen, didn't you?

104
00:05:49,399 --> 00:05:50,199
Captain Li,

105
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,600
that's a sharp remark.

106
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:58,920
From the day I learned the Chengming loan had issues,

107
00:05:59,439 --> 00:06:01,040
I haven't slept soundly.

108
00:06:01,759 --> 00:06:03,439
Let alone Director Shen.

109
00:06:05,279 --> 00:06:08,240
After all, she handled all the paperwork herself.

110
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,800
But as things stand,

111
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:16,560
the matter hadn't reached a dead end.

112
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,639
She wouldn't take her own life over it.

113
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,079
Unless...

114
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,160
Maybe I'm overthinking it.

115
00:06:27,319 --> 00:06:28,120
It's unlikely.

116
00:06:29,279 --> 00:06:30,680
Often, the things that seem impossible

117
00:06:31,160 --> 00:06:32,600
turn out to have more possibilities.

118
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:35,319
So please, tell us everything you know.

119
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:37,519
It might help with our case.

120
00:06:40,560 --> 00:06:43,759
Perhaps Director Shen already knew beforehand

121
00:06:45,519 --> 00:06:47,759
the actual state of Chengming Machinery's operations.

122
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,399
Are you saying

123
00:06:58,439 --> 00:07:01,160
that Director Shen deliberately hid the truth from you

124
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:03,120
and secretly helped Chengming Machinery

125
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:04,680
obtain the loan?

126
00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:07,800
I'm just guessing.

127
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:10,759
We'd need an internal investigation to confirm.

128
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,800
But personally speaking,

129
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,360
I still have great trust in Director Shen.

130
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:24,519
Boss, the moment we moved to investigate Shen Qing,

131
00:07:24,519 --> 00:07:25,360
she fell to her death.

132
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,680
Could she have been silenced?

133
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:30,199
As cops, we must never blindly guess or prejudge.

134
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:32,839
Remember this.

135
00:07:33,319 --> 00:07:35,639
Every case is like an intricate puzzle.

136
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,879
Each piece seems independent,

137
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,240
but is actually tightly connected to the rest.

138
00:07:41,759 --> 00:07:42,680
So what we have to do

139
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,199
is unravel the mystery piece by piece,

140
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:45,240
until the puzzle is complete.

141
00:07:46,879 --> 00:07:48,279
Between Shen Qing and Chengming Machinery,

142
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:49,639
there must be a hidden secret.

143
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:51,319
Otherwise, she wouldn't be afraid of the Economic Crimes Unit's probe.

144
00:07:53,279 --> 00:07:54,160
This Su Zhuang,

145
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,519
what do you make of him?

146
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,439
He seems very cooperative,

147
00:07:58,759 --> 00:08:00,720
but quietly deflects all responsibility.

148
00:08:01,279 --> 00:08:02,879
Like he wants to tell us something,

149
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,600
yet seems to be deliberately hiding it,

150
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:05,720
keeping us in the dark.

151
00:08:06,199 --> 00:08:07,240
Spoken like a true bank president.

152
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,600
A master at passing the buck.

153
00:08:09,199 --> 00:08:09,839
What else?

154
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,439
He must know that trouble for the credit director

155
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:13,600
would trigger a butterfly effect.

156
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,240
He seems to be in a tough spot,

157
00:08:16,319 --> 00:08:19,079
but he actively exposed the massive fraud

158
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:21,000
between Shen Qing and Chengming Machinery.

159
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:23,399
That way, he answered our questions

160
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,720
while clearing himself of suspicion.

161
00:08:25,319 --> 00:08:26,079
What's more,

162
00:08:28,399 --> 00:08:29,120
Go on.

163
00:08:30,439 --> 00:08:32,039
I think he's deliberately steering us

164
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,200
to subconsciously believe it was suicide.

165
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,000
Good, you're thinking like a detective.

166
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,919
Of course, Boss.

167
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,360
I read books and papers every day.

168
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,799
Isn't that so I can use it in investigations?

169
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,519
After Shen Qing entered the bank,

170
00:08:47,679 --> 00:08:49,759
she took the side fire stairs up to the rooftop.

171
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,759
Soon after she got up there, the power went out.

172
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,960
And every external camera went dead.

173
00:08:54,919 --> 00:08:57,360
The odds of such a coincidence are way too low.

174
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,320
If you were Shen Qing,

175
00:09:02,759 --> 00:09:03,720
in a moment like that,

176
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,559
how would you choose to jump?

177
00:09:07,159 --> 00:09:09,440
Boss, your hypothetical is kind of creepy.

178
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,639
From the day you enter the police academy,

179
00:09:13,639 --> 00:09:15,200
you must learn to face life and death calmly.

180
00:09:15,879 --> 00:09:16,720
To crack a case,

181
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:19,159
putting yourself in their shoes is often the most effective.

182
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:23,080
Boss, you put yourself in her shoes instead.

183
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,159
I can't really imagine

184
00:09:25,159 --> 00:09:26,960
how a woman would feel in such a moment.

185
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,399
But you're different.

186
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:30,039
You can't relate?

187
00:09:30,039 --> 00:09:31,120
Well, I can't relate either!

188
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,399
I'm a rock-solid hardcore straight guy.

189
00:09:33,519 --> 00:09:34,320
Don't you always say

190
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,919
you're especially good at psychology?

191
00:09:36,519 --> 00:09:37,759
What a great chance to show it off.

192
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:38,519
No, wait,

193
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,240
just let me show what I can do.

194
00:09:44,039 --> 00:09:45,000
Hold on, I-I-I'll

195
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:45,879
get a feel for it.

196
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:48,200
Get up there and feel it.

197
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:01,559
Go on, up.

198
00:10:16,879 --> 00:10:17,519
So how was it?

199
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:19,120
What did you feel?

200
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:20,879
Dizzy.

201
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:22,399
My head's spinning.

202
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:25,919
I felt this intense weightlessness,

203
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,919
like there was a whirlpool below,

204
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:30,639
sucking me right in.

205
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:34,559
Is this all from a woman's perspective?

206
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:35,679
Of course.

207
00:10:35,919 --> 00:10:37,279
You've got to really get into the character.

208
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:41,159
I think Shen Qing was extremely vain and image-conscious.

209
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,799
She'd probably fuss for a whole week

210
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:44,559
over just a tiny scrape.

211
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:46,639
If she'd jumped face-first,

212
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,240
she'd be completely disfigured.

213
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:49,240
That's not a choice she'd make.

214
00:10:59,159 --> 00:11:00,960
Alright, you're really in character.

215
00:11:01,919 --> 00:11:02,720
What about jumping backwards then?

216
00:11:18,159 --> 00:11:19,519
Facing backwards is even more unlikely.

217
00:11:19,519 --> 00:11:20,399
It's terrifying.

218
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,120
No normal person would ever do that.

219
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:25,080
So when a person stands backwards up high,

220
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,799
a woman's subconscious reaction

221
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,639
is that her arms will involuntarily

222
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:29,919
wrap tightly around her body.

223
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,360
It's the brain's self-protection mechanism kicking in.

224
00:11:34,039 --> 00:11:35,320
I think men would do the same.

225
00:11:38,279 --> 00:11:39,600
Unless an external force was applied,

226
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:48,919
otherwise, when Shen Qing fell,

227
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,679
she wouldn't have landed so far out.

228
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:55,039
So there's no way Shen Qing committed suicide.

229
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,000
Boss, I'm heading down now.

230
00:12:17,279 --> 00:12:18,480
Hello, sorry to bother you again.

231
00:12:18,879 --> 00:12:19,679
There are some things

232
00:12:19,679 --> 00:12:21,120
we need to ask you about further.

233
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,960
I've already made myself perfectly clear.

234
00:12:23,039 --> 00:12:24,559
I went to bed early last night.

235
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:25,600
I didn't hear a thing.

236
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:26,840
As a citizen,

237
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,039
you have a duty to cooperate with the police.

238
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,080
And as a citizen,

239
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:31,519
I also have the right to remain silent.

240
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:35,600
Captain Li,

241
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:40,120
this female neighbor of Shen Qing's

242
00:12:40,639 --> 00:12:42,440
seems really resistant to our questions.

243
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,960
I feel like she must know something.

244
00:12:55,679 --> 00:12:57,279
Did Forensics find anything here?

245
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,360
Both floors are spotlessly clean.

246
00:12:59,519 --> 00:13:00,919
After Forensics examined the scene,

247
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:02,440
they found no suspicious traces.

248
00:13:03,039 --> 00:13:04,840
No signs of an intruder.

249
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,039
Spotlessly clean.

250
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,759
This shows Shen Qing really was a clean freak.

251
00:13:34,159 --> 00:13:34,799
Oh, by the way

252
00:13:35,279 --> 00:13:37,600
There's a very unusual room upstairs

253
00:13:38,399 --> 00:13:39,639
You'll see what I mean in a minute

254
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,240
Let's say Shen Qing did kill herself

255
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:44,360
Before doing so

256
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,759
would she really clean every corner

257
00:13:45,759 --> 00:13:47,000
of the house until it was spotless,

258
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,960
then grab a beer and jump off the bank's rooftop?

259
00:13:50,639 --> 00:13:51,480
Does that make any sense?

260
00:13:52,919 --> 00:13:55,679
People are highly unstable before a suicide

261
00:13:57,360 --> 00:13:59,399
Having a drink to comfort herself isn't unusual

262
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,639
As for the cleaning

263
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:04,000
a woman living alone

264
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,120
even if she skipped a day or two

265
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,759
the place wouldn't look that messy, right?

266
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:54,679
When you shower

267
00:14:54,879 --> 00:14:56,600
hair usually gets caught in the drain

268
00:14:56,879 --> 00:14:58,200
especially long hair

269
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,679
Shen Qing had just showered before she died

270
00:15:01,039 --> 00:15:02,960
but there's not a single strand of hair here

271
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,279
How do you know she showered?

272
00:15:05,679 --> 00:15:08,080
Because she smelled of shampoo and body wash

273
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:11,000
If she hadn't showered shortly before her fall,

274
00:15:11,399 --> 00:15:12,639
the scent wouldn't be that strong

275
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,559
Shen Qing left the bank at 7:20

276
00:15:17,679 --> 00:15:19,320
I just drove here from the bank

277
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,360
It took 25 minutes

278
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:21,440
Factoring in rush hour

279
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,240
she'd have been home by 8:10 at the latest

280
